Aplicaciones TJ does not collect physical addresses or banking details directly nor gathers precise location data.
Security measures are in place to protect all this data against unauthorized access. These measures are both online and offline, and in cases where additional data such as full name, address, credit card numbers, among others are required for purchases or services; these data are collected by external platforms, which are well recognized worldwide as secure payment gateways.

Data Share:
Bookshelf secures students' data access and only permits students, teachers, and administrators granted permission by the district to access it. American Reading Company does not share Bookshelf data with third parties unless instructed by district administration. While aggregated information about book usage is provided to publishers, this does not include specific student, school, or district information. Bookshelf does not contain advertising, and no collected data is used to drive targeted advertising.
Data Collect:
American Reading Company collects data for rostering students and classrooms in Bookshelf. The information collected includes name, username, password (with encryption), district identifier, school assignment, classroom assignment, IP address, and IDs for different log in systems. For educators specifically, email addresses are collected. For students, additional data including date of birth, gender, ethnicity, Title I Status, Special Education Status, English Learner Status, and student performance data may be collected. The data is not collected directly from students or family members, rather from school or district administrators and teachers via different formats and mechanisms.

privacy_policy_content:
Data Share:
Auto-Data.net does not share your personal data publicly. When you visit the site, some information may be automatically recorded from your device, including IP address, browser type, and access times. This is done to enhance your experience and provider safety and security. Your information will be stored on servers within the European Union.
Third-party services such as Google Analytics are used to analyze how users interact with the site. Google Analytics uses cookies to assess site usage and activity - this information will be transmitted to Google servers in the United States. Data may be stored in cookies when you log into your account, including your username and hashed password.
In the context of advertising, third-party companies may store information about your visits to Auto-Data.net and other websites to provide relevant advertisements about goods and services. These companies may use cookies and other identifiers to measure advertising effectiveness.
Data Collect:
Auto-Data.net collects your email address, username, password, and IP address. The email address is retained to secure your account and provide high-quality support as needed. Your username and password are collected to facilitate account logins. Your IP address is processed to deter "spam"-like behavior.
Automatic data collection also occurs when you visit the site, including recording from your device, web pages visited before and during your time on the site, and the dates and times of your visits.
If you create an account, your email, username, and password are held for 24 hours pending email confirmation. If no response is received after 24 hours, this data is permanently deleted. Once confirmed, your personal data is kept for 60 months after your last use of your account.
Furthermore, if you use the contact form on the site, your email address is processed to provide a quality support experience.

privacy_policy_content:
Data Share:
Trainchinese BV does not sell, trade or rent Personally Identifiable Information collected on the site. User's personal details are kept on the company's servers in a manner that can only be accessed by the user, identified by their username and password. While the app versions and device information are stored on the server, this data is used to create an anonymous token that identifies the device. It's essential for synchronizing multiple devices and troubleshooting. Should the user request, Trainchinese BV will delete their account and associated server data, but any public contributions to discussions will retain the user’s trainchinese username.
Data Collect:
When users register at trainchinese, personal details are collected to create an account. This can include voluntary information such as name, country of residence, languages spoken and level of Chinese. The site also collects website usage details, information about the user's computer and internet connection, the type and version of the browser and operating system used, and the URL of the linking page if arriving via a link from another website. The app keeps detailed information on the vocabulary learned by the user and their training activities. Functionalities such as Optical Character Recognition (OCR) and speech recognition require images and audio to be captured and processed respectively. In case of purchases or transactions, the services of third parties are employed to process credit card payments securely, meaning Trainchinese BV does not have direct access to credit card data.

These partners could use the data for ad relevance, search product enhancement, fraud prevention on sponsored search results, and research.
2. Assistants: Yahoo may share data collected through Assistants, including conversations, interactions, Yahoo ID, and account information. This could be shared with third-party services interacting with the Assistants, including the user's account with the third-party, user ID, name, photo, phone number, email, and device information.
3. Yahoo Shopping: When making a purchase, the merchant receives customer personal information directly. Yahoo Shopping does not collect or use this data.
Data Collect:
1. Search Services: Yahoo collects information when a user conducts a search. This includes user's search queries, individual search history, search result clicks, and data from private results. Yahoo also uses image recognition to facilitate image searches and collects data from tracking URLs in search results.
2. Assistants: Yahoo collects user data through its Assistants, which include user conversations, interactions, Yahoo ID, and associated account information. Additional data may also be collected from third-party services interacting with the Assistants, including account and device information of the user.
3. Yahoo Shopping: Shopping data collection is carried out by PriceGrabber. When a purchase is made from a merchant, the merchant asks for personal data including name, shipping and billing addresses, email, telephone number, and credit card details.

Our partnership with Samsung allows users' home appliances, TVs, and devices to be linked and controlled via their Galaxy phones or smart monitors. We extend this partnership to elevate the smart home experience offered by SmartThings Station and Hub Everywhere feature.

privacy_policy_content:
Data Share:
Upon registration, we may share your details with Urban Point Merchants to update you on deals, news, and special offers. This information may be shared with specific Merchants when requested, to facilitate offer redemption. Any personal data shared with Merchants occurs only if you engage in an Identification Activity, and it's restricted to the Merchant involved. Note, this may allow a Merchant to directly market to you. Although we instruct Merchants to use this information only for specific promotion with Urban Point, we cannot control their actions and thus, disclaim any liability for their actions.
Data Collect:
We collect your information upon registration on Urban Point. This data might include your e-mail, contact number for updates, news, and special offer notifications. In specific situations, Merchants may also access some of your Personally Identifiable Information to assist in offer redemption when you engage in an Identification Activity.

privacy_policy_content:
Data Share:
The Explore app does not share your email address with third parties. The app periodically transmits anonymized, aggregated data to external services to aid in improving the app and the associated services. The Good Book Company may share your information with third parties as described in the privacy statement. Information may be disclosed as required by law or to trusted service providers who work on their behalf, strictly adhering to the guidelines set in the privacy statement. The app utilizes third-party services that have their own privacy policies about data handling.
Data Collect:
The Explore app allows you to link your email address with the app for cross-device access to purchased reading plans. This email address is stored if this feature is used. The app collects diagnostic data to improve performance and stability, including a limited log record and device-related data from the occurrence of any bugs or glitches. This data does not contain personal information. The app also collects analytics data when you download and use it. This includes your device's IP address, visited app pages, time spent on the app, and the mobile operating system used. This aggregated, anonymized data aids The Good Book Company in analyzing user behavior and improving the app. The app does not knowingly collect personally identifiable information from children under 13. Any breach of this will lead to the immediate deletion of such data.

- You share your personal data with THALES SIX GTS France SASU while using Citadel service. The data may be shared with other Citadel users upon your manual approval.
- The shared data can include your user location, photos, and videos from your photo gallery or phone camera.
- As part of Citadel's services, your data may be used to authenticate your user profile, identify people you communicate with, manage support requests, and send recommendations from your address book.
- Citadel may need to make the requested data available to legal authorities for compliance with applicable regulations.
- In specific cases, your employer (the Customer) may have access to some of your personal data when Citadel is available as a subscription with a fleet management option.
- Some data might be transferred out of the European Economic Area (EEA) to the country where the Customer is located. In such a case, THALES ensures to implement appropriate safeguards.

- THALES collects and uses your data for provisioning Citadel services, compliance with legal requirements, and other purposes including but not limited to ensuring Citadel's security, user communication, service improvement, and for litigation management.
- Mandatory personal data provision is required for the contract's conclusion. In its absence, THALES might not be able to provide requested services.
- Your personal data is kept as long as required by the type of processing: one year from collection for connection logs, one year from the deactivation of the account for account-related information, and during the contractual relationship and applicable legal limitation period for litigation management.
- Customers not using Citadel for eleven months will be notified, and the non-responsive ones will have their accounts and related data deleted.
- THALES observes all data subject rights including access, rectification, and deletion of personal data. You also have the right to data portability for your information processed via automated means. Queries or complaints can be addressed via email to relevant THALES addresses.

Data Share:
1. Data Protection and Disclosure to Affiliates and Third Parties
UKG doesn't sell personal data to third parties. Personal data may be shared with UKG affiliates to facilitate product or service delivery or complete tasks as requested by the users. It may also disclose user data to third-party vendors or service providers for various purposes like product delivery, training, marketing, and site optimization on contractual terms which ensure compliance with confidentiality and data protection rules. Personal information may additionally be disclosed for customer service, compliance with legal obligations, litigation management, security and fraud prevention, business transactions such as mergers or acquisitions, and user consent.
2. Transferring Personal Information
UKG agrees to use Standard Contractual Clauses or the UK International Data Transfer Agreement for transferring user data to third-party subprocessors. UKG complies with EU-U.S. and Swiss-US Data Privacy Framework, UK-U.S. Data Privacy Framework and APEC's Cross Border Privacy Rules System for international data transfers. UKG may be required to disclose personal data in response to lawful requests by public authorities including meeting national security or law enforcement requirements.
Data Collect:
1. Collection of User Information
UKG collects personal data from several sources including direct user interaction, service providers, and third parties. Information collected includes personal details such as name, company, job title, address, phone number, email address, and data related to user's interaction with the site.
2. Usage of Collected Data
The collected data is used by UKG to fulfill user inquiries and requests, improve their products and services, market their offerings, and ensure site security. In some circumstances, UKG may use user data for product and services training, litigation management, auditing, and legal compliance.
3. Retention of Collected Data
UKG retains user data for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes for which it was collected or as required by applicable laws. Depending on the nature and sensitivity of the data, UKG may securely store, deidentify, or delete the information when it's no longer needed.
4. Data Subject Rights
Depending on the user's location, individuals may have specific rights regarding the collection, usage, and sharing of their personal data. These rights include access to personal data, the ability to update or correct inaccurate data, request data deletion, and file complaints about UKG's data processing practices.

privacy_policy_content:
Data Share:
1. Service Providers: Information may be shared with service providers and affiliated parties such as website or database hosting companies for operating and maintaining the website or delivering services. However, there are strict contractual restrictions to prevent the misuse of the shared information.
2. Aggregated Statistics: Non-personally identifiable aggregated user behavior statistics may be disclosed to third parties. This information is collected through third-party cookies and tracking devices.
3. Legally Compelled Disclosures: Personal information may be disclosed if required by law or subpoena, or if it’s believed necessary to comply with legal processes, protect rights, property, and safety.
4. Third-party Websites: The Website may have links to other websites, which could collect personal data about users. Those websites are not covered by this privacy policy.
5. Consent to Worldwide Transfer and Processing: Users agree to the transfer and processing of their information in different jurisdictions which may have varied privacy laws.
Data Collect:
1. Cookies: Cookies are used to improve user experience on the Website. Users’ personal information could be related to the data provided from the cookies.
2. Clear GIFs: Clear GIFs or similar techniques are used in the Website and communications with users to determine viewing or receipt of web pages.
3. IP Address and Clickstream Data: The servers automatically collect data about your Internet Protocol address and other web usage activity and data. This data does not personally identify the users.
4. Personal Information: Users have the choice to opt-in or opt-out of the use of their personal data for certain purposes. However, users might still be contacted about their relationship, activities, transactions and communications with the site.
5. Third-Party Websites: Visiting or linking to other websites may result in those websites collecting Personal Information about the users. Those websites have their own privacy policy that differs with this one.
6. Personal Information from Minors: The website does not knowingly collect personal information from children under the age of thirteen. If it is discovered such information is collected, it will be deleted.
7. Security Measures: Industry-standard measures, including SSL encryption for sensitive information, are used to maintain the integrity and security of Personal Information.

privacy_policy_content:
Data Share: Content
The University Privacy team provides guidance and resources to help navigate Cornell's regulatory obligations and ethical principles related to the curation and use of data. In collaboration with units, colleges, and departments across campus, we work closely with Cornell Information Technology to realize these goals aligned with Cornell's core values. We also facilitate solutions and balance compliance with mission-driven activities.

Our team is focused on enhancing a culture of compliance and ethics. We support Cornell's mission of learning, discovery, and engagement, while upholding Cornell's core values in data collection. We are dedicated to understanding and managing how data is collected, stored, and used within the Cornell community.
